lenders.name: Annie
lenders.loan_because: Microfinance in general is a reasonable way to provide financial services to the poor. I loan because I want to support women´s empowerment. Women are the poorest of the poor. Women in particular benefit from access to credit because from experience the ability to generate income from an own business improves their livelihoods AND that of their children. Furthermore economic activities, responsibility for a credit and financial independency improve the social status of women because financial resources in the hand of women have an impact on power relations and participation.

lenders.name: The Lois and Olivia Fund
lenders.loan_because:
This fund was created to honour our maternal grandmothers, Lois Light and Olivia Seal.  

In September 2008, our wedding guests donated about $3700 to get the fund started.

In 2012, Linda Light donated her retirement gift of $500 to the Lois & OIivia Fund.

And our most recent "party with a purpose" - the first annual Saturday House Hootenanny 2012 was a raging success, bringing in $400 for new loans!

We continue to build the fund and love using it to support the excellent work of Kiva and entrepreneurs across the globe.
